      - 17
    kind: note
    message: Workspace root Cargo.toml already listed `paths_walk`, so no root edit was needed.
    reasoning: The prompt forbade touching the root manifest while requiring `cargo test` to pass from the root — those conflict if the root does not list the new member. Agent reports the root already listed `paths_walk`, so no conflict materialized; agent added `paths_walk/Cargo.toml` with a single `extensions = { path = "../extensions" }` dependency.
  - promptLines:
      - 21
      - 24
    kind: ambiguity
    message: '"do not depend on any hand-written crate" is unexplained and near-contradicts depending on `extensions`.'
    reasoning: The clause sits immediately after an instruction to depend on `extensions` (a workspace crate that is itself hand-written), so its scope is unclear — it may mean "no vendored/local crates other than workspace members" or "no third-party crates at all". Agent read it as the latter and shipped with `extensions` as the sole dependency, hand-rolling the temp-dir helper rather than pulling `tempfile` or `walkdir`.
    suggestion: Depend only on the `extensions` workspace crate; add no third-party dependencies (no `walkdir`, no `tempfile`).
  - promptLines:
      - 54
      - 54
    kind: note
    message: Test relies on `extensions::default_prompt_aliases()` returning `Vec<String>`; unverified against extensions' actual signature here.
    reasoning: Line 54 names the function but not its return type. The call site passes `&extensions::default_prompt_aliases()` directly into a `&[String]` parameter, which only compiles if it returns `Vec<String>` (or `[String; N]`). Agent reports the workspace `cargo test` is green, so the shape matched.
